        <updateDate>2008-03-19T20:57:45Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Terrorism Risk Insurance Improvement Act of 2007 - Amends the Terrorism Risk Insurance Act of 2002 to revise the definition of &quot;insurer deductible&quot; with respect to a situation where aggregate industry insured losses resulting from a certified act of terrorism exceed $1 billion for an insurer that sustains any of such losses.</p> <p>Sets forth a calculation for the value of such an insurer's direct earned premiums over the calendar year immediately preceding the program year.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
